<emphasis id="81786910A99028BD98A241A0E147C946" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea abutiloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is especially so in the state of Bahia, where it is typical of caatinga vegetation. In Bolivia it is much less common than 
<taxonomicName id="0E7BEBC3E5D12397F59650CE10D71E15" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="abutiloides">
<emphasis id="D44218E07FC3133F7D2D692D4BCD2EED" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. abutiloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
